The paper discusses a web-based logging architecture that records and analyzes user actions while using computer-based mathematics tools. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze user actions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses privacy concerns and the need to respect learner privacy, which suggests that it may belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to analyze user actions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of web-based tools to support teachers in understanding learner actions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Education (cs.CE) sub-category.
